---
description: Handle Isambard SSH auth expiry via Clifton
alwaysApply: true
---

# Isambard Clifton Auth

- Isambard SSH certificates expire every ~12 hours and are refreshed with `clifton auth`.
- If SSH fails with `Permission denied (publickey)` or `Connection closed by remote host`, stop retries.
- Ask the user to run `clifton auth`, then continue only after they confirm auth is complete.
- Do not attempt to run `clifton auth` from the agent.
- After user confirmation, retry exactly the original SSH command.
